[49.684133, "o", "peg's codec parsers, it is expected that this generally causes fewer issues than cuda.\u001b[8;17HMost  video  filters  will not work with hardware decoding as they are primarily imple\u001b[9;17Hmented on the CPU. Some exceptions are vdpaupp, vdpaurb and vavpp.  See  VIDEO  FILTER\u001b[10;17Hfor more details.\u001b[12;17HThe  ...-copy  modes  (e.g. dxva2-copy) allow you to use hardware decoding with any VO\n\u001b[3G\u001b[0;7m\u001b(B\u001b[38;5;7m\u001b[48;5;0m              \u001b[0;7m\u001b(B\u001b[38;5;1m\u001b[48;5;0mbackend\u001b[0;7m\u001b(B\u001b[38;5;7m\u001b[48;5;0m or filter. Because these copy the decoded video back  to  system  RAM,  they'r\u001b[14;17H\u001b[0m\u001b(B\u001b[38;5;7m\u001b[48;5;0mlikely  less  efficient  than the direct modes (like e.g. dxva2), and probably not mor\u001b[15;17Hefficient than software decoding except for some codecs (e.g. HEVC).\u001b[17;17HNOTE:\n\b\bWhen using this switch, hardware decoding is still only done for  some  codecs.  Se\u001b[19;20H--hwdec-codecs to enable hardware decoding for more codecs.\u001b[1;33H\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u001b(B"]
